added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Dance Crew Edition Part 1
added.description: It's time for another Justice League talent competition and Vibe is joining the judges' panel to critique the moves of the DC universe dance crews.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Dance Crew Edition Part 2
added.description: Robin is left without a dance crew so Vibe gives him lessons on how to be a world class break-dancer and team player.

added.title: Forest Pirates
added.description: The Titans are at Super Hero Summer Camp for the week and they may need to add another teammate to win the big canoe race.

added.title: Communicate Openly
added.description: Bumbleebee becomes the 6th Titan and moves into the Tower but has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Royal Jelly
added.description: Bumblebee offers to help Robin with his leadership skills by teaching him how to act like a queen bee.

added.title: The Viewers Decide
added.description: It's Titans West vs Titans East as the two teams compete for who gets Bumblebee.

added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: How 'Bout Some Effort
added.description: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend Jinx.

added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: Smile Bones
added.description: When Cyborg and Beast Boy teach the other Titans to wolf down their food, the gang develops a big fat problem.

added.title: The Return of Slade
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

added.title: Be Mine
added.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

added.title: Opposites
added.description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

added.title: Little Buddies
added.description: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: Adopted
added.description: The Baby Bears get adopted by an eccentric millionaire and get to live in his mansion.

added.title: Braces
added.description: When the Bears go to the dentist, Panda gets braces. But, Panda finds out his braces grant him super abilities and the power goes to his head.

added.title: Bubble
added.description: Panda becomes a germophobe and decides to live the rest of his life in a bubble.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: Dance Lessons
added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.title: Bunnies
added.description: The Baby Bears meet a group of helpless bunnies. When they find out the bunnies live in fear of vicious crows, the Bears decide to become heroes and help out.

added.title: Baby Bears Can't Jump
added.description: In order to win a pizza, the Baby Bears play basketball against a ragtag gang of kids.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Anybody
added.description: Gumball wants Clayton to sit his detention for him, so he convinces him it's way more exciting to be take the shapes of other people.  However, Clayton begins imitating people all over town and causing mayhem. Gumball and Darwin have to convince him that the most exciting person to be is himself.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Console
added.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

added.title: The Comic
added.description: Gumball is the star of his own comic, but struggles to match up to his heroic alter-ego.

added.title: The Romantic
added.description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

added.title: The Advice
added.description: Mr. Small feels that he hasn't inspired the children of Elmore Junior High, so Gumball and Darwin try to lift his spirits.

added.title: The Love
added.description: The residents of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

added.title: The Misunderstandings
added.description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Dream
added.description: When Gumball blames Darwin for kissing Penny in his dream it threatens to tear apart their friendship, the only place you can fix a dream problem is in the dream world.

added.title: The Dress
added.description: Gumball goes to school in a dress and becomes the darling of Elmore High.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: Omni-Copped
added.description: When Grandpa Max's engineer buddy Phil Billings gifts Team Tennyson the Omni-Copter, a state of the art flying vehicle that can transport the Rustbucket for overseas adventures, Steam Smythe takes to the skies to ground Ben and company's first test flight; but unbeknownst to our heroes, Smythe was sent to battle Ben's latest alien forms by a mysterious, powerful enemy: the Forever Knight.

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Bridge Out
added.description: After an overpass collapses on the highway, Team Tennyson is in a traffic jam along with Simon Sez and family. But when Ben and Simon team up to tackle the gridlock together, Simon only makes matters much, much worse.

added.title: Charm School's Out
added.description: During a family cookout at a forest campsite, Charmcaster users her magic to switch places with Gwen, but when Ben catches "Charmcaster" sneaking about, he attacks, unaware it's actually his cursed cousin!

added.title: Franken-Fight
added.description: Ben hops into the Rustbuggy for a driving lesson along the sand dunes of Cape Cod, but he takes a freaky switchback turn when the Rustbuggy is mutated into a motor-monster by Bootleg, another alien transformation of Kevin 11, with powers similar to Upgrade!

added.title: Which Watch
added.description: After a battle with Kevin gets mysteriously cut short, Ben turns his attention to one upping Gwen at Space Camp. But, when his arch-nemesis, Kevin, returns with his sights strangely set on his cousin, our hero must uncover who is really behind it all, Charmcaster!

added.title: Them's Fightin' Words!
added.description: After enjoying some local corn, Team Tennyson discovers a Hartfield-McJoy reenactment in the cornfield next door, but when Hex resurrects the ghosts of the real feuding families, Ben must find a way to bring them together if he is to save the day!

added.title: The Chupaca-bro
added.description: Team Tennyson discovers that a small village's goats are being terrorized by the legendary Chupacabra, but when Ben realizes it's actually Dr. Animo, our hero must thwart the dastardly doctor before he uses the essence of the goats to power up into an unstoppable form!

added.title: Introducing Kevin 11
added.description: At a local swap meet, Ben instead sets his sights on a Sumo Slammer collectible, but when Kevin takes it for himself, our hero must get it back by overcoming Kevin's secret weapon: an 11th alien!

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Hole in 10
added.description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

added.title: Recipe for Disaster
added.description: During Chefapalooza in the Rocky Mountains, three famous chefs and infamous bad-guys, The Tri-Chefta, hunt down Wildvine in hopes of creating their most exotic dish to date.

added.title: The Ground Is Lava!
added.description: When an intense game of "The Ground is Lava" breaks out, Craig must carefully traverse the Creek to save his sister.

added.title: Fort Williams
added.description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: In the Key of the Creek
added.description: When a rainy day keeps Craig inside, he uses his toys and imagination to create his own Creek adventure in Craig of the Creek's first musical episode!

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Gum and Gummer
added.description: Beth gets her gum stuck in Leshawna's hair and has to get it out - without Leshawna finding out it's there.

added.title: Invasion of the Booger Snatchers
added.description: Harold believes that the picture day photographer is somehow turning the kids into well behaved zombies.

added.title: Wristy Business
added.description: Beth and Leshawna try to one-up each other with fake injuries as they compete for the attention and sympathy of the other kids at daycare.

added.title: Melter Skelter
added.description: When Chef tells Beth he won't buy the new super amazing toy she wants because they already have plenty to play with, she goes on a mission to get rid of their toys.

added.title: The Never Gwending Story
added.description: When Chef loses the last page of the story-time book, Gwen takes over and creates a monster that all the kids start to believe in.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple helps Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: Apple and Onion need to join an exclusive club to see a rare whale.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: Apple and Onion must find a way to use Burger's trampoline without making him feel used.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: Level Thirteen
added.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

added.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
added.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Brotherly Love
added.description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 1
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 2
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: Exodus Part 1
added.description: Fleeing the destruction of their home planet Thundera, Lion-O and the ThunderCats land on the mysterious, dangerous, all-around awesome world of Third Earth! But their enemies, the Mutants of Plun-Darr have followed them and it turns out Third Earth already has a Mumm-Ra problem, can Lion-O learn the ropes of being a leader in time?

added.title: Exodus Part 2
added.description: Fleeing the destruction of their home planet Thundera, Lion-O and the ThunderCats land on the mysterious, dangerous, all-around awesome world of Third Earth! But their enemies, the Mutants of Plun-Darr have followed them and it turns out Third Earth already has a Mumm-Ra problem, can Lion-O learn the ropes of being a leader in time?

added.title: The Legend of Boggy Ben
added.description: Lion-O has gotten a hold of the last jar of Thundersnaps, the best cookies Thundera had to offer! But a difficult to open cookie jar is gonna send Lion-O and Cheetara chasing down a legend, a Boggy Ben-related legend.

added.title: Prank Call
added.description: Lion-O wants to prove to the ThunderKittens that he's not just some boring old adult, like Tygra, even if it means ignoring his instincts and messing with an obviously evil crystal.

added.title: Driller
added.description: Panthro is getting a little fed up with having to fix things around the Cats' Lair constantly, which is unfortunate because the ThunderCats are about to be attacked by an unstoppable drilling robot, and he's gonna break everything!

added.title: Sadie Killer
added.description: Steven and the Cool Kids start a band, but they have trouble finding their sound.

added.title: Pool Hopping
added.description: Garnet and Steven explore the most unlikely timelines in Beach City.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: Legs from Here to Homeworld
added.description: Steven travels to visit family.

added.title: Tiger Philanthropist
added.description: Steven returns to the ring to continue his pro wrestling odyssey.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Bubble Buddies
added.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

added.title: Tiger Millionaire
added.description: Steven joins Amethyst in an underground wrestling league.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: On the Run
added.description: Steven and Amethyst try out life on the road.

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: No Shortcuts
added.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: He's the Sheriff
added.description: The gang struggles to get rid of the King when he joins them as their new deputy-for-a-day!

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Cherry Cream Soda
added.description: With the arrival of an impossible visitor, Cherry Cream Soda's life is thrown into disarray.

added.title: Angel Face
added.description: BMO ropes his friends into a live action cowboy role-playing adventure!

added.title: Bad Jubies
added.description: There's a catastrophic storm headed for the Grasslands so Finn, LSP and BMO decide to build a bunker for protection, but Jake has plans of his own.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: Astral Plane
added.description: Finn has an out-of-body experience that takes him all over Ooo and beyond.

added.title: The Suitor
added.description: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

added.title: Love Games
added.description: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sis. Finn steps in to save the day but first they will need to win a series of love games to prove to Slime Princess's dad that they are really in love.

added.title: Apple Wedding
added.description: You are cordially invited to the wedding of the year! But who will be united in matrimony?

added.title: The Red Throne
added.description: When Flame King breaks out of his prison and takes over the Flame Kingdom again, Flame Princess turns to the one person she believes she can trust, Finn!

added.title: Dream of Love
added.description: Tree Trunks is courted by an oinking suitor, but much to Jake's dismay, this interferes with her baking habits.

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess. Is Princess Bubblegum jealous?

added.title: Incendium
added.description: Jake sets Finn up with the Flame Princess with fiery results.

added.title: Go With Me
added.description: Finn needs to date to the movies and must balance the contrasting advice of Jake and Marceline in wooing Princess Bubblegum so he can see that flick!

added.title: Prisoners of Love
added.description: The boys try to cool off but get trapped by the Ice King.

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Career Day
added.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

added.title: Asteroid Blues
added.description: An asteroid is headed right for the kingdom, so Dr Fox leads the gang on a mission to save the kingdom by flying a rocket to the asteroid's surface and blowing it to bits with a huge bomb. But when they get there the gang finds the lonely asteroid is actually a super nice guy and don't want to blow him up.

added.title: Brock Most Wanted
added.description: When Master Frown starts ruining parties to earn a promotion from his bosses, the Doom Lords, Brock accidentally gets blamed for the calamity. He helps Frown ruin more parties to clear his name and prove he's not the real party pooper, but before long Brock is the most notorious criminal in the kingdom, and the Doom Lords hire him as Master Party Pooper. Desperate to get his promotion and save his friend, Master Frown recruits Unikitty to ruin one last party, Brock's Doom Lord initiation ceremony.

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Buggin' Out
added.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

added.title: Chair
added.description: Unikitty finds an old, beatup recliner on the curb, but sees its inner beauty and brings it home to introduce to the gang! In a series of absurd and fun vignettes, we discover how a dirty, inanimate chair comes into each of their lives and changes them for the better. We soon learn that dear, sweet Chair was too good for this world.

added.title: Brawl Bot
added.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

added.title: La mascara del engano
added.description: Cuando un sindicato de criminals desconocido amenaza a la Familia Real, los ninjas son llamados de nuevo a la acción y deben proteger a la princesa real y un artefacto legendario que puede tener poderes sobrenaturales.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Mask of Deception
added.description: When an unknown criminal syndicate threatens the Royal Family, the Ninja are called back into action and must protect the royal princess and a fabled artifact that may hold supernatural powers.

added.title: La princesa de jade
added.description: A raíz de un cruel ataque al Palacio, Los Hijos de Garmadon roban la segunda Máscara Oni, y los ninjas invitan a la Princesa Real, Harumi, a su improvisada familia.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Jade Princess
added.description: In the wake of a vicious attack upon the palace, the Sons of Garmadon steal the second Oni Mask, and the ninja invite the royal princess, Harumi, into their makeshift family.

added.title: El oni y el dragon
added.description: Mientras que la Princesa Harumi se adapta a la vida con los ninjas, Lloyd y Jay buscan respuestas sobre las máscaras Oni, mientras que Cole y Zane intentan infiltrarse en Los Hijos de Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Oni & the Dragon
added.description: While Princess Harumi adjusts to life with the ninja, Lloyd and Jay search for answers about the Oni Masks, while Cole and Zane attempt to infiltrate the Sons of Garmadon.

added.title: Guar serpiente
added.description: Para unirse a Los Hijos de Garmadon, Zane (alias Jaguar Serpiente) participa en una carrera de iniciación mortal de motocicletas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Snake Jaguar
added.description: In order to join the Sons of Garmadon, Zane (aka Snake Jaguar) participates in a deadly motorcycle initiation race.

added.title: El chillido de hombre muerto
added.description: La casi desaparición de Zane a manos del Señor "E" obliga a los ninjas a huir a bordo del Bounty, donde descubren que una tramisión que Zane interceptó puede revelar la ubicación oculta del "Silencioso".
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dead Man's Squall
added.description: Zane's near demise at the hands of Mr. E forces the ninja to flee aboard the Bounty, where they discover that a transmission Zane intercepted may reveal the hidden location of the Quiet One.

added.title: Benson's Pig
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to take Benson's new pet pig back to his apartment.

added.title: La Incomodidad
added.description: Gumball y Chico Salchicha descubren por qué se sienten tan incómodos el uno con el otro.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Benson's Suit
added.description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: Bank Shot
added.description: Rigby has to win a bet by beating a guy at basketball bank shots.

added.title: Comunicacion abierta
added.description: Bumblebee se convierte en la sexta Titán y se muda a la torre, pero tiene problemas para adaptarse.

added.title: El publico decide
added.description: iEn un duelo entre los Titanes Oeste y los Titanes Este, ambos equipos compiten para decidir quien se queda con Bumblebee!

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Frenos
added.description: Cuando los Osos van al dentista, Panda se coloca frenos. Pronto, descubre que los frenos le confieren habilidades superiores y ese poder se le sube a la cabeza.

added.title: The Tunnel
added.description: After Clarence accidentally knocks Belson's new video game down a storm drain, Belson enters the large underground sewer tunnel to retrieve it. When Belson doesn't return, Clarence must decide whether or not to go in after him.

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Burbuja
added.description: Panda comienza a sufrir de fobia a los gérmenes y decide vivir el resto de su vida en una burbuja.

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
added.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

added.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
added.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

added.title: Bet to Be Blonde
added.description: Rigby wins a bet with Mordecai and makes him get a blonde perm.

added.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
added.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

added.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
added.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

added.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
added.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

added.title: Land of the Lost Shadows
added.description: When pieces of their shadows are stolen by a shadow demon, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must travel to the Land of Lost Shadows in order to retrieve them.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Memory Foam
added.description: When a new mattress sucks away all of Pizza Steve's memories, Uncle Grandpa and the crew must find a way to get them back.

added.title: Lights Out!
added.description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: The Judge Part 1
added.description: The Quintesson Judge and his forces assault Iaconus while Optimus and Megatron lead a strike team into the Quintesson ship.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: The Judge Part 2
added.description: Megatron and Optimus's strike team faces off against the Scientist while the Autobot and Decepticon defenders of Iaconus desperately keep the all-powerful Judge distracted.

added.title: The End of the Universe I Part 1
added.description: Starscream's fate at the hands of the Quintessons is revealed as he returns a three-headed Judge!

added.title: The End of the Universe I Part 2
added.description: Judge Starscream interrogates his Cybetronian prisoners while Optimus, Bee, and Wheeljack try to get back through the Multiverse Bridge.

added.title: The End of the Universe II Part 1
added.description: Windblade battles the Sharkticons to regain entry into Iaconus.

added.title: The End of the Universe II Part 2
added.description: While the Autobots and Decepticons stall Judge Starscream, Windblade tries to awaken Iaconus.

added.title: Conejos
added.description: Los Osos bebés conocen a un grupo de conejos indefensos. Cuando descubren que los conejos viven aterrados de unos cuervos despiadados, los Osos deciden convertirse en héroes y ayudarlos.

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: Framed
added.description: Kevin 11 is back and out for revenge. And with the ability to shape-shift into several of Ben's alien heroes, he's been framing Ben for his crimes.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Hundred Dollar Gus
added.description: Pizza Steve makes up a preposterous lie that lands the gang in big trouble.

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: Final Exams
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up with an unlikely ally to take on an unlikely foe.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Jay Estrella del Rock
added.description: Dentro de Primer Imperio, los ninjas se encuentran en un territorio desconocido e intentan encontrar a Jay y escapar de los Visores Rojos de Unagami.

added.title: Nexo Creativo
added.description: Cuando KO queda atrapado dentro de un lugar misterioso, se encuentra con otros héroes de Cartoon Network y todos se unen para escapar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
added.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

added.title: Isla Dyer
added.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Yo Soy Okino
added.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

added.title: Examenes Finales
added.description: KO, Enid y Rad se unen a un aliado improbable para enfrentarse a un enemigo improbable.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Nivel Trece
added.description: Cyrus Borg descubre un secreto sobre Primer Imperio y  los ninjas enfrentan al Mecánico que escapó e intenta alcanzar el Nivel 13 para entrar al juego.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Primera parte
added.description: En el episodio estreno de cuatro partes de la serie, seis chicas comunes y corrientes se conocen y descubren que tienen poderes extraordinarios. Deciden unir sus fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: The Mystery of Loch-Mess
added.description: The Warriors are sent on a mission to Loch Mess to locate missing deliverymen only to find themselves captured as pets for the giant piggy Queen Porcina.

added.title: Squirreled Domination
added.description: Rare food enthusiast Fud sends the Warriors on a mission to the Deepest Darkest Woods to gather five golden acorns from a golden oak tree for a golden acorn casserole, but poor Vambre has a secret fear of squirrels, and it turns out that golden squirrels are the scariest of them all!

added.title: La Leyenda del Parque Patinetas
added.description: Mientras buscan un parque de patinaje escondido, V y V se encuentran con una tribu de niños salvajes, que viven en una sociedad sin reglas ni adultos.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.

added.title: Surely You Jest-O
added.description: House sitting for Omnibus is boring work for the Warriors, but their decision to allow Jest-O and his Taunting Jester Magisword come in from the rain to entertain them turns out to be their worst idea yet!

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: Nuclear Family Values
added.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

added.title: Zombie King
added.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: Galaxy Jest
added.description: Joker is abducted into space by Mongul to entertain Mongul's troops. Unless the Justice League can re-capture him in time, a Joker gas bomb will go off in Gotham threatening the city.

added.title: Derrota aplastante
added.description: Cuando Hawkodile se enamora en secreto de la Dra. Fox, idescubre que comienza a encogerse en tamaño! Como está demasiado avergonzado como para contárselo a ella (o a cualquiera), Unikitty y la pandilla se convierten en sus gurús del amor para ayudarlo a confesar sus sentimientos antes de encogerse hasta desaparecer.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Repulse!
added.description: Luthor infects Superman with a magnetic charge that repels everything. As the repulsing charge grows, the Magnetized Man of Steel is fated to spend the rest of his life isolated in space unless the Justice League can figure out a way to free him.

added.title: El Oso De Arriba
added.description: Cuando Panda se tropieza y, por accidente, ahuyenta a una manada de lobos, la jerarquía de los Osos se ve alterada. De pronto, Panda se convierte en el oso alfa, y Ice junto a Pardo deben lidiar con las consecuencias de tener a un Panda sensible como líder de los tres Osos.

added.title: Joyride
added.description: At a rummage sale with Uncle Andrew, Axel and Zoe must stop Madcap from turning her long-lost tank toy, Joyride, into an agent of mayhem!

added.title: Savage Axel
added.description: Bearbarian helps Axel get in touch with his wild side as Orangutank "liberates" nature from an apartment building - tossing potted plants of all sizes out the window and onto innocent bystanders below!

added.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.

added.title: Manana Es Hoy
added.description: Cuando Max arrastra a los niños a ver una "Casa del futuro" obsoleta construida por su ídolo de la infancia, Ben descubre que Vapor Smythe está ocupado excavando el lugar en busca de un dispositivo poderoso que le permitirá crear armas devastadoras para su guerra en progreso. Solo la devoción de Max por su ídolo de la infancia y la fe de Ben en los sueños puede salvar el mañana...ihoy mismo!

added.title: Lectura, Que Aburrido
added.description: Durante una firma de libros en un castillo medieval, Ben debe impedir que Hex se apodere de un grimorio que puede fusionar a su lector con bestias míticas...iy así crear híbridos monstruosos!

added.title: Hoyo En 10
added.description: Mientras Ben juega al minigolf, lo atacan los Ground Hawgs, una pandilla de mutantes convertidos en ciclistas del Doctor Ánimo. Pero cuando los Hawgs se dan cuenta de que la falsa aldea de minigolf no es un lugar real, Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para detenerlos antes de que elijan la ciudad verdadera que está a pocos metros de allí como su blanco.

added.title: Receta Del Desastre
added.description: Durante el festival gastronómico Chefapalooza en las Montañas Rocosas, el Tri-Chefta, compuesto por tres cocineros famosos y villanos infames, persigue a Wildvine con la esperanza de crear el plato más exótico que jamás hayan preparado.

added.title: Bichos
added.description: Cuando Unikitty y la banda descubren un bicho asqueroso en el castillo, están desesperados por deshacerse de él para siempre, pero Unikitty se niega a permitir que lo aplasten, no importa qué tan asqueroso o peligroso parezca. ¿Qué tipo de red está tejiendo Unikitty para sus amigos?

added.title: Sillon
added.description: Unikitty encuentra una vieja silla reclinable en la acera, pero ve su belleza interior y lo lleva a casa para mostrárselo a la pandilla. En una serie de situaciones absurdas y divertidas, descubrimos cómo una silla sucia e inanimada entra en cada una de sus vidas y las cambia para mejor. Pronto aprendemos que la querida y dulce silla era demasiado buena para este mundo.

added.title: El Destino de un Heroe
added.description: Cuando un héroe que desapareció hace mucho se topa con la tienda de Gar, K.O. acepta ayudarlo a completar su misión que dura años.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: A Hero's Fate
added.description: When a long lost hero stumbles into Gar's, KO agrees to help him complete his years long quest.

added.title: Pelea Bot
added.description: La Dra. Fox se enorgullece de presentar su nueva máquina de combate definitiva y llevarla a un ring de combate científico subterráneo. Pero Hawkodile está celoso del bot de combate de la Dra. Fox, que supuestamente da mejores golpes que él, y declara que puede vencer a cualquier cosa que el bot pueda. Para demostrar su afirmación, se viste con piezas de robot de repuesto y entra en secreto en la batalla de robots. Con Unikitty como su entrenadora de lucha, ¿podrá Hawkodile sobrevivir al torneo, demostrar que es más fuerte que una máquina y salvarse del depósito de chatarra?

added.title: Goma pegajosa
added.description: A Beth se le atasca la goma de mascar en el cabello de Leshawna y tiene que sacarla- sin que Leshawna descubra que está ahí.

added.title: Invasion de los mocos ladrones
added.description: Harold cree que el fotógrafo del día de la foto oficial está convirtiendo a los niños en zombies que se portan bien.

added.title: Mentiras lastimosas
added.description: Beth y Leshawna tratan de superarse uno a la otra con heridas falsas mientras compiten por la atención y comprensión de los otros niños en la guardería.

added.title: KO's Video Channel
added.description: Enid and Rad discover that KO has a video channel.

added.title: Derretidor
added.description: Cuando Chef le dice a Beth que no comprará el nuevo juguete súper increíble que ella quiere porque ya tienen mucho con qué jugar, ella emprende una misión para librarse de sus juguetes.

added.title: La historia de nunca Gwenminar
added.description: Cuando Chef pierde la última página del libro de cuentos, Gwen se hace cargo y  crea un monstruo en el que todos los chicos comienzan a creer.

added.title: De vuelta a la accion roja
added.description: Enid se alía a Acción Roja para enfrentarse a una amenaza del futuro.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: Back in Red Action
added.description: Enid teams up with Red Action to take on a menace from the future.

added.title: Hide and Secrets
added.description: Desperate for answers about Namagem, Mega Man decides to break into his father's lab, which leaves Suna exposed to the vengeful robot.

added.title: Make the Cut
added.description: Mega Man goes on a 24/7 heroing spree around the city, forcing Suna, Bert, Ashley, and Rush to deal with the problem at hand, Cut Man.

added.title: Panic in the Lighthouse
added.description: When Chaotique breaks into Dr. Light's lab, Mega Man must shut down his frenemy and the lab's defenses before either of them gets destroyed!

added.title: Collect This
added.description: Ben finally meets the ones responsible for his intergalactic TV show, and the actor who makes Ben 10 more famous than Ben himself!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 2
added.description: As Dr. Light and Suna turn the Robot Masters against each other, Mega Man defeats and unmasks his arch nemeses, Lord Obsidian, who turns out to be Sgt. Night in disguise, and finally learns the identity of Namagem, Mega Man's long lost twin brother!

added.title: Charm School
added.description: At Gwen's college, Ben suspects a new teacher and new student are old enemies.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: Soy Mi Monstruo
added.description: No todo está bien.

added.title: Todo Esta Bien
added.description: Steven insiste en que todo está bien.

added.title: La Broma
added.description: Cuando intenta demostrarles a los Thundercachorros que no es un adulto aburrido (como Tigro), León-O ignora sus instintos y se mete con un cristal claramente malvado.

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

added.title: Exodo Parte 2
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: Papel de Bano Bebecin
added.description: Manzana necesita conseguir la provisión del papel higiénico que usaría en toda su vida para terminar su escultura de arte moderno.

added.title: Fragmentos
added.description: Steven se dirige al bosque para entrenarse con un poderoso mentor.

added.title: Lucha de Pulgares
added.description: El trío decide concursar en la competencia anual de Lucha de Pulgares, pero una sorpresa obliga a Mao Mao a lidiar con algo impensado… la derrota.

added.title: Joyride
added.description: iEn una venta de artículos usados ​​con el tío Andrew, Axel y Zoe deben evitar que Madcap convierta su juguete tanque perdido, Joyride, en un agente de caos!

added.title: Conquista de Popularidad
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao descubre que no es tan popular como Colosal y Adorabat, sus amigos deciden reinventarlo en forma de un héroe más amable y tierno.

added.title: Rumbo al Planeta Madre
added.description: Steven acude a las Diamantes para pedirles consejos sobre cómo controlar sus nuevos poderes.

added.title: El es el Sheriff
added.description: iEl trío lucha por deshacerse del Rey cuando los acompaña como nuevo ayudante del sheriff por un día!

added.title: La Leyenda de Boggy Ben
added.description: León-O se apoderó del último frasco de Thundersnaps, ilas mejores galletas disponibles en Thundera! Pero un frasco de galletas difícil de abrir hace que León-O y Chitara terminen yendo tras la leyenda de Boggy Ben.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Colosal adopta a un monstruo abandonado, pero es mejor dejar algunas cosas en estado salvaje.

added.title: Exodo Parte 1
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: Revienta Fiestas
added.description: Los planes de la fiesta de Manzana y Cebollín son interrumpidos por un invitado malhumorado.

added.title: El Salvaje Axel
added.description: Bearbarian ayuda a Axel a ponerse en contacto con su lado salvaje mientras Orangutank "libera" la naturaleza de un edificio de apartamentos, arrojando plantas en macetas de todos los tamaños por la ventana y hacia personas inocentes que se encuentran debajo.

added.title: Todo Por Mao Mismo
added.description: El deseo de Mao Mao de convertirse en leyenda lo lleva a querer superarse a sí mismo una y otra vez. ¿Pero cuánto es suficiente?

added.title: Taladro
added.description: Pantro se está hartando de tener que arreglar cosas constantemente por todo el Cubil Felino, lo cual es una pena porque los Thundercats están a punto de ser atacados por un robot perforador imparable...ique va a romper todo!

added.title: No es Gracioso
added.description: Cuando se acerca el aniversario de seis meses de amistad, Manzana tiene que encontrar una manera de no perder a su mejor amigo.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet "n" Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: Gatocalipsis
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma y debe reposar en su cuarto, espía a Piña y queda convencido de que está creando un ejército de gatos zombis. Val está de acuerdo con él y ambos se obsesionan con detener a Piña antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: Dendy's Power
added.description: Dendy and KO discover a fun and exciting new POW Card exploit.

added.title: Bittersweet Rivals
added.description: Enid is forced to confront lingering issues from a past friendship.

added.title: Are You Ready for Some Megafootball?!
added.description: Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.

added.title: Second First Date
added.description: Love is in the air and Cupid arrives to resolve romantic tension around the plaza.

added.title: Rad Likes Robots
added.description: Rad finds love in an unexpected place.

added.title: The Perfect Meal
added.description: KO teams up with Beardo to make the perfect meal for Carol.

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Sneaky Peeky
added.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Nano of the North
added.description: It's raining in Townville, but this is more than just rain. These drops are actually microscopic robots tearing apart the city, and the girls must find a way to fight them on their own level.

added.title: Pee Pee G's/Boy Toys
added.description: The Pee Pee G's: When the girls wake up to discover their bed is wet, none of them want to admit that they are the guilty party./Boy Toys: The girls allow Princess to become a Powerpuff Girl when they realize they need help trying to defeat the Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Nuthin' Special/Neighbor Hood
added.description: Nuthing Special: Frustrated with not knowing what her special power is, Buttercup hunts to discover what makes her special./Neighbor Hood: When everyone on Bubbles' favorite show loses their happy, Bubbles helps bring it back.

added.title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
added.description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Powerprof.
added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
added.description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Bubbles the Blue
added.description: When Bubbles isn't her normal, bubbly self, her sisters don't know how to handle it.

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: Snow Month
added.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

added.title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
added.description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Working for Scales
added.description: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

added.title: Potion in the Ocean
added.description: Witchy Simone joins the Warriors on a mission deep in the Fickle Sea to find an eye of newt for her magic potion, but Man Fish the Fish Man won't let them harm his sea newt pal!

added.title: Bad Bad Cop
added.description: Vambre and Prohyas pretend to be cops in their attempts to shakedown a dangerous bunch of pirates to find a broccoli smuggler.

added.title: Thick as Thieves
